The paper deals with the robustness of BERT, a state-of-the-art model in NLP, in dealing with noisy data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are covered in sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses sentiment analysis and question answering benchmarks, which are related to natural language processing and machine learning, but may also fall under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
